{"TopicId":205212,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"Making part upgrades?","CreatedByName":"WarpPrime","CreatedById":210576,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-10T21:37:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"WarpPrime","CreatedById":210576,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-10T21:37:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to make part upgrades in my mod, but I don\u0027t know how. Is there any way I can do this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-10T21:47:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like a MODULE config node can contain an UPGRADES config node which contains UPGRADE config nodes that define the upgrades:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002298962\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7254830954\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/147623-the-new-stock-partupgrade-functionality/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:192px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theJesuit","CreatedById":122369,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-12T09:00:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224041885\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205212\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221633901840\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210576\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022WarpPrime\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/11/2021 at 10:37 AM, WarpPrime said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to make part upgrades in my mod, but I don\u0027t know how. Is there any way I can do this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome modules can be upgraded but not all.\u00A0 You also can\u0027t add modules to a part \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u00A0only change them.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EBut for an example look at my SIMPLEX Propulsion mod.\u00A0 You\u0027ll see the upgrade created and then added to the part.\u00A0 These are are engine ones.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EAlso a part that has \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E functionality changed is the avionics nose cone in both the SIMPLEX and TETRIX TechTrees.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-12T17:10:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been working (slowly) on a part upgrade mod - which in my humble opinion has been sorely needed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif you can find them - Tyco? had some engine upgrade patches\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}